data.enText: a way of addressing sb that you love
a person who is very friendly and kind
a person who is especially liked and very popular

data.chText: 她是新闻界的大红人，不可能做错事的。
data.enText: She is the darling of the newspapers and can do no wrong.

data.chText: 备受喜爱的；可爱的；迷人的
data.enText: much loved; very attractive, special, etc.

data.chText: “亲爱的亨利”，信的开头这样写道。

value.def: You call someone darling if you love them or like them very much.
In some parts of Britain, people call other people darling as a sign of friendliness.
value.tran: (英国一些地方用于表示友善的称呼）亲爱的

value.def: Some people use darling to describe someone or something that they love or like very much.

example.ex: To have a darling baby boy was the greatest gift I could imagine...
example.tran: 生一个可爱的男孩是我能想到的最好的礼物。

example.ex: What a darling film — everyone adored it.
example.tran: 多么令人着迷的一部电影啊——所有人都非常喜欢。

value.def: If you describe someone as a darling, you are fond of them and think that they are nice.
The darling of a group of people is someone who is especially liked by that group.

example.ex: Rajneesh was the darling of a prosperous family.
example.tran: 罗杰尼希是一个富有家庭的宠儿。
